etwork,\\\" the spokesperson said.\", \"from\": 1783, \"to\": 1908, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"between three and eight other operators\", \"from\": 1790, \"to\": 1829}, {\"ngram\": \"our long-distance network\", \"from\": 1858, \"to\": 1883}, {\"ngram\": \"the spokesperson\", \"from\": 1886, \"to\": 1902}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nicolas Guillaume, the CEO of telecom firm Nasca Group, which owns the ISP company Netalis, told WIRED he believed the damage was \\\"deliberate\\\" and that ISPs serving both customers and businesses have been impacted.\", \"from\": 1910, \"to\": 2124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1953, \"end\": 1958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazca_culture\", \"score\": 0.9677358052064527, \"rank\": 0.03333987907829059, \"text\": \"Nasca\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazca_culture\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazca_culture\"}, {\"begin\": 1981, \"end\": 1984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Internet_service_provider\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5775588682433128e-37, \"text\": \"ISP\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Internet_service_provider\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Internet_service_provider\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Nicolas Guillaume\", \"from\": 1910, \"to\": 1927}, {\"ngram\": \"the CEO\", \"from\": 1929, \"to\": 1936}, {\"ngram\": \"WIRED\", \"from\": 2007, \"to\": 2012}, {\"ngram\": \"the damage\", \"from\": 2025, \"to\": 2035}, {\"ngram\": \"ISPs\", \"from\": 2062, \"to\": 2066}, {\"ngram\": \"both customers\", \"from\": 2075, \"to\": 2089}, {\"ngram\": \"businesses\", \"from\": 2094, \"to\": 2104}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Several of the damaged cables,according to images shared on Xby the CEO, appear to have clean cuts across them.\", \"from\": 2125, \"to\": 2236, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the damaged cables\", \"from\": 2136, \"to\": 2154}, {\"ngram\": \"images\", \"from\": 2168, \"to